SUBCONTRACTS FOR COMMERCIAL PRODUCTS OR COMMERCIAL SERVICES (
            NOV 2023
            )

(
           b
           )(1) In accordance with 10 U.S.C. 3457(c), the Contractor shall treat as commercial products any items valued at less than $10,000 per item that were purchased by the Contractor for use in the performance of multiple contracts with the Department of Defense and other parties and are not identifiable to any particular contract when purchased.
